Herb Holland with Tanya Holland Lavelle and 5 others.
· December 31, 2016 · Austin, TX ·

Today is the day when we try and make sense of what's happened in the past year. Sorry ... just can't make this happen in 140 characters.

Certainly there were a "few disappointments," but I'm thankful for the wonderful things that happened to me and my family during 2016.

It was a great year for business. I love my clients and am grateful for the opportunities we had to stretch ourselves creatively and intellectually.

...

It was a great year for music. I love my many bandmates and the hundreds/thousands in my extended music family and am grateful for the opportunities I had in 2016 to make beautiful sound with some of the most creative people in Austin, in Texas, the USA and the entire planet! (say that three times on one breath!)

It was a great year for travel and exploration. I love my travel partner, Genevieve Holland. and am grateful we never run out of adventures! Can't wait for our next great adventure... next week.

Most of all, it was a great year to be a Dad! We are so proud of our children and the closeness we all share. Where did we go right? Oh yeah ... and this happened too!

Bring it on 2017. I know you're going to start AND end in style! What happens in between is up to us!
